\pard\ql\sl480\slmult1 \b \f0\fs24 6.2 System Changeover / Installation\b0 \par
\pard\ql\sl480\slmult1 \b \f0\fs24 6.2.1 Direct Changeover\b0 \par
\pard\qj\sl480\slmult1 \f0\fs24 Direct changeover replaces the old system immediately and carries higher risk.\par
\pard\ql\sl480\slmult1 \b \f0\fs24 6.2.2 Parallel Changeover\b0 \par
\pard\qj\sl480\slmult1 \f0\fs24 Parallel changeover runs the old and new systems together for comparison.\par
\pard\ql\sl480\slmult1 \b \f0\fs24 6.2.3 Phased Changeover\b0 \par
\pard\qj\sl480\slmult1 \f0\fs24 Phased changeover introduces the system in modules or stages.\par
\pard\ql\sl480\slmult1 \b \f0\fs24 6.2.4 Pilot Changeover\b0 \par
\pard\qj\sl480\slmult1 \f0\fs24 Pilot changeover introduces the system first to a limited environment before full rollout.\par
\pard\ql\sl480\slmult1 \b \f0\fs24 6.2.5 Recommended Changeover Method\b0 \par
\pard\qj\sl480\slmult1 \f0\fs24 Pilot changeover supported by phased deployment is the most suitable method for this project.\par
